Empire of Carolina Inc., Tarboro, N.C., said it has begun preliminary merger talks with Clabir Corp. and AmBrit Inc., although no timetable has been set for the discussions. 

In addition, Clabir, based in Clearwater, Fla., said it will ask shareholders in December to approve a recapitalization proposal effecting a 100-for-1 reverse stock split of the company's Class A and Class B common stock.
The company said its proposal would also call for conversion of Class B common and preferred stock into Class A common stock after the reverse split. 

Clabir said it has outstanding 16,290,682 shares of Class A common stock and 1,141,628 shares of Class B common, and 3,988,746 shares of preferred stock. 

Clabir conducts its business primarily through AmBrit, in which it holds a 76.5% stake.
AmBrit makes frozen novelty and confectionary products.
Empire makes toys, decorative items, and buttons. 

Empire, along with members of the family of Maurice Halperin, controls Clabir.
Mr. Halperin is chairman and chief executive officer of the three companies. 

